[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Zechariah 7:9-12",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Zechariah 7:9-12",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thus speaketh the Lord of hosts — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or did speak, that is, to your fathers, and thus he speaks to you now; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Execute true judgment — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I often put your fathers in mind that judgment and mercy were more acceptable to me than fasting, or any external performances; (see the margin;) and I repeat the same admonition to you of the present age. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And let none of you imagine evil against his brother, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Neither think ill of, nor wish ill to, nor plot evil against one another. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But they refused to hearken ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— But your fathers refused to obey the admonitions of the former prophets, and were often reproved by them for their refractory disposition; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and pulled away the shoulder — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Withdrew their shoulder from the yoke of the law. The metaphor is taken from oxen that refuse to put their necks under the yoke. See the margin. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Yea, they made their hearts as an adamant-stone — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So that no arguments could make any impression upon them; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "lest they should hear the law — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of God by Moses, which they were peremptorily required to do, but to do which they as peremptorily refused; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and the words — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The counsels and commands; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "which the Lord hath sent in his Spirit by the former prophets — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Inspired and commissioned his prophets to declare; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "therefore — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For this great obstinacy; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "came a great wrath — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which consumed the whole land, and burned against the people that had inhabited it seventy years together in Babylon; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "from the Lord of hosts — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In all which the hand of the Lord was most evidently seen, rendering unto them according to their ways.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7:8-14 God's judgements upon Israel of old for their sins, were written to warn Christians. The duties required are, not keeping fasts and offering sacrifices, but doing justly and loving mercy, which tend to the public welfare and peace. The law of God lays restraint upon the heart. But they filled their minds with prejudices against the word of God. Nothing is harder than the heart of a presumptuous sinner. See the fatal consequences of this to their fathers. Great sins against the Lord of hosts, bring great wrath from his power, which cannot be resisted. Sin, if regarded in the heart, will certainly spoil the success of prayer. The Lord always hears the cry of the broken-hearted penitent; yet all who die impenitent and unbelieving, will find no remedy or refuge from miseries which while here they despised and defied, but which they then will not be able to bear.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thus spake the Lord - that is, through the former prophets, for he goes on to speak of their rejection in the past. \"Execute true judgment.\" He retains the words of Ezekiel. The injunction itself runs throughout the prophets. \"Shew mercy\" (as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 58:6-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 7:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 18:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hosea 12:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.), that is, tender love, to all; compassion, to the unhappy. Omit no act of love, God so loves the loving. Lap.: \"Like Paul to the Romans Rom 13:9, he names only the duties to the neighbor, but understands what relates to God. For the love of our neighbor presupposes the love of God, from which it springs.\" Jerome: \"After strictness of justice, let mercy to all follow, and specially to brethren, of the same blood and of one faith. Brother and neighbor we ought to account the whole human race, since we are all born of one parent, or those who are of the household of faith, according to the parable of the Gospel, \"which willeth us to understand by neighbor, nor our kin, but all men\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 10:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9. speaketh—implying that these precepts addressed to their ancestors were the requirements of Jehovah not merely then, but now. We must not only not hurt, but we must help our fellow men. God is pleased with such loving obedience, rather than with empty ceremonies.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Thus speaketh, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or did speak, i.e. to your fathers, and thus he doth speak to you now. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Execute true judgment:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " God required former judges, and he requireth present judges, without hatred, prejudice, partiality, or bribery to give true sentence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Show mercy and compassions; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " be kind and beneficent to such as need; wrong none if you could; do good to all you can with tenderest and most abundant pity, with a heart that feels their miseries. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Every man; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as this is every man’s duty, let it be every one’s practice. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "To his brother, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. to every one that needs you. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
