  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thus speaketh the Lord of hosts, saying,.... The same things as he had before; for the things following are ever in force, and always to be attended to, and to be regarded and preferred before anything merely ritual and ceremonial; and especially before the traditions and commandments of men, of which nature the above fasts were: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Execute true judgment; or, \"judge judgment (e) of truth\"; this is addressed to the judges of the people, that when any cause came before them between man and man, that they would judge righteously, according to the law of God; and, without respect to persons, pass sentence as the truth of the case required: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and show mercy and compassion every man to his brother; whether in want of food, raiment, or in whatsoever distress, whether of body or mind; which is much more acceptable to God than any legal sacrifices, or outward abstinences and humiliations, Hosea 6:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and show mercy and compassion every man to his brother; whether in want of food, raiment, or in whatsoever distress, whether of body or mind; which is much more acceptable to God than any legal sacrifices, or outward abstinences and humiliations, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hosea 6:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e)  \"judicium veritatis\", Montanus, Calvin, Cocceius, Burkius; \"jus veritatis\", Junius & Tremellius, Tarnovius. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(e)  \"judicium veritatis\", Montanus, Calvin, Cocceius, Burkius; \"jus veritatis\", Junius & Tremellius, Tarnovius. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
